Whirlpool Hires 1,100 in Brazil Following Tax Cut, Estado Says

-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r i s t o w
-- 
2011-12-11T14:58:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-11/whirlpool-hires-1-100-in-brazil-following-tax-cut-estado-says.html
Whirlpool Corp.’s (WHRL4)  Brazilian unit
will hire 1,100 factory workers on 120-day contracts to meet an
expected first-quarter sales surge because of a  tax cut  on home
appliances, O Estado de S.Paulo newspaper  reported , citing Jose Drummond, the company’s president of Latin American operations.  Brazil ’s government this month cut taxes on stoves,
refrigerators and washing machines as part of a stimulus
package.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Matthew Bristow in Brasilia at 
 mbristow5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Joshua Goodman  at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 